# 🗺️ Deliverable 4: System Architecture & Design (Day 52)

This document establishes the official technical foundation, data design, and architecture for **SmartStudy AI** based on the PRD created on Day 51.

---

## 1. Technical Stack Justification

| Component | Technology | Selection Justification |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Frontend & UI** | **Streamlit** | Eliminates JavaScript/HTML overhead, enables rapid Python-only rendering, and fits the strict 10-day deployment constraint perfectly. |
| **Backend Logic** | **Python 3.10+** | Provides seamless native integration with Streamlit frameworks and the standard Anthropic API wrapper. |
| **Database Engine** | **SQLite (Local Storage)** | Zero configuration needed, runs serverless out of a single local file, and provides structured storage for historical analytics. |
| **Authentication** | **Session State (Local)** | Bypasses complex OAuth implementations for v1.0. User states persist dynamically during the execution session. |
| **AI Processing** | **Claude 3.5 Sonnet API** | Superior capabilities in JSON formatting, textual summarization, complex contextual logical reasoning, and structured educational output. |
| **Public Hosting** | **Streamlit Cloud** | Direct structural synchronization with our public GitHub repository, providing instantaneous hot-reloads on git pushes. |

