## 3. Database Schema Design (SQLite Engine)

To support the analytics dashboard and save flashcard status without managing complex cloud databases, we will implement the following structured tables:

### 📋 Table 1: `quiz_history`
Manages performance logging for user test metrics over time.

*   `id` (INTEGER, Primary Key, Auto-Increment)
*   `topic_name` (TEXT, Not Null) — Extracted target header or manual title.
*   `total_questions` (INTEGER, Not Null) — Default value set to 5.
*   `score_achieved` (INTEGER, Not Null) — Number of accurate user responses.
*   `completion_timestamp` (DATETIME, Default CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)

### 📋 Table 2: `saved_flashcards`
Manages localized retention items generated via the AI helper.

*   `id` (INTEGER, Primary Key, Auto-Increment)
*   `term_front` (TEXT, Not Null) — Concept title, vocabulary item, or core question.
*   `definition_back` (TEXT, Not Null) — Expanded logic description or verified definition.
*   `is_mastered` (INTEGER, Default 0) — Flag toggled between 0 (Learning) and 1 (Mastered).

